{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Vanilla Butter","content":["Preheat oven to 220°C and line a baking tray with baking paper.","Place sugar and clementine peel in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>20 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour, butter and baking powder then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>.","Add buttermilk and poppy seeds then mix <nobr>20 sec\/<\/nobr>. Tip out onto a lightly floured surface and bring together into a ball. Flatten to 2.5 cm thick then use a pastry cutter (Ø 6 cm) to cut out scones and place on prepared baking tray. Re-roll and cut any trimmings to make 8 scones.","Brush scones with beaten egg then bake for 12-15 minutes (220°C) until golden brown. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and prepare butter."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Scones","content":["35 g caster sugar","2 clementines, thin peelings of skin only","250 g self-raising flour, plus extra for dusting","60 g salted butter, cold, diced","1 tsp baking powder","120 g buttermilk","2 Tbsp poppy seeds","1 egg, beaten"]},{"title":"Vanilla Butter","content":["150 g salted butter, soft","1 tsp vanilla bean paste"]}],"id":"r133700","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-VkK2LfCZYr0\/XZWrZHdZrJI\/AAAAAAAAfms\/30RL7Lc2BrM1F5kDwDoI9u8fxSuKeHMZQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_kcIxTuuMIbDMgQiA.png","title":"Clementine and Poppy Seed Buttermilk Scones","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.4 g","fat":"22.1 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"33.2 g","calories":"1459 kJ \/ 349 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and paper, round pastry cutter (Ø 6 cm), pastry brush, small serving bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["The butter can be made ahead then rolled up in cling film into a log shape and placed in the fridge. Slices can then be served to accompany the scones.","Scones are best served the day they are made."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","30m","8 pieces"]}